---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Background, skills, research interests, and long-term goals.">
  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Background, Skills, and Direction</h1>
    <p>
      I am <strong>Horace Chan</strong>, a mechanical engineering undergraduate student interested in the intersection
      of mechanical systems, intelligent agents, and AI-assisted research workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      This website is a long-term public space for projects, learning notes, experiments, reading paths, and reflections
      as they become concrete.
    </p>

    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      My academic background is in <strong>Mechanical Engineering</strong>. I am building a foundation in mechanical
      design, robot systems, machine learning, deep learning, and robot control, while gradually connecting these areas
      through practical projects and reading notes.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am especially interested in how engineering intuition from physical systems can support the study of embodied
      AI and robotic control.
    </p>

    <h2>Engineering Skills</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Mechanical structure design with mainstream 3D CAD tools, including SolidWorks</li>
      <li>Programming with Python, C, and C++</li>
      <li>Learning and applying machine learning and deep learning fundamentals</li>
      <li>Building structured study systems and AI-assisted workflows for technical learning</li>
      <li>Reading and organizing papers, project notes, and implementation records</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Research Interests</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>AI-assisted workflows</strong> for learning, research, note-taking, and engineering productivity</li>
      <li><strong>Vision-Language-Action models</strong> and their role in robot learning</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Embodied AI</strong>, especially the connection between perception, language, action, and physical
        interaction
      </li>
      <li><strong>Robotics and robot control</strong>, including modeling, control strategies, and learning-based methods</li>
      <li>Mechanical design for intelligent robotic systems</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Long-Term Goal</h2>
    <p>
      My long-term goal is to understand how intelligent agents and robot systems are constructed, from mechanical
      design and control to learning-based decision-making. I hope to participate in research and engineering practice
      related to embodied intelligence, robot control, and AI-assisted scientific workflows.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
